[2026-05-19T02:18:46.939Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_3ekv6g1aggvv_1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task: 012-article-reader-03-convert\n2\t\n3\t# Convert: Article Reader\n4\t\n5\tConvert the constrained HTML design to a pixel-perfect Flutter widget using the **stitch-flutter** skill.\n6\t\n7\t## Inputs\n8\t- `.stitch/designs/article-reader/design.html` — HTML design mockup (written in Flutter HTML Glossary vocabulary)\n9\t- `.stitch/designs/article-reader/SPEC.md` — Screen specification\n10\t- `.stitch/system/DESIGN.md` — Design system specification\n11\t\n12\t## How It Works\n13\t\n14\tThe HTML mockup uses the **Flutter HTML Glossary** — a constrained vocabulary where every HTML class and `data-*` attribute maps 1:1 to a Flutter widget. This enables mechanical, pixel-perfect conversion.\n15\t\n16\t## Conversion Steps\n17\t\n18\t1. **Read HTML** — Parse `.stitch/designs/article-reader/design.html` and extract:\n19\t   - `:root` CSS tokens → update `lib/theme/app_theme.dart` if new tokens found\n20\t   - `.scaffold` element tree → this is the conversion entry point\n21\t   - `data-*` attributes → Flutter widget parameters\n22\t   - `data-animate` attributes → `flutter_animate` chains\n23\t   - `aria-*` attributes → `Semantics` widgets\n24\t\n25\t2. **Walk the DOM** — Process each glossary element top-down:\n26\t   - `.scaffold` → `Scaffold()`\n27\t   - `.app-bar` → `AppBar()`\n28\t   - `.column` → `Column()`\n29\t   - `.row` → `Row()`\n30\t   - `.card` → `Card()`\n31\t   - `.ink-well[data-route]` → `InkWell(onTap: () => context.push(route))`\n32\t   - `.network-image` → `CachedNetworkImage()`\n33\t   - `.icon[data-name]` → `Icon(Icons.{name})`\n34\t   - Text classes (`.title-large`, `.body-medium`, etc.) → `Text(..., style: textTheme.X)`\n35\t   - `data-color` → `colorScheme.X`\n36\t   - `data-spacing` → `AppTheme.spaceX`\n37\t   - `data-radius` → `AppTheme.radiusX`\n38\t\n39\t3. **Generate Dart**