70	| Card tap | 200ms scale to 98% | Press feedback |
71	
72	## 6. Layout Rules
73	
74	### Scaffold Structure
75	```
76	Scaffold
77	├── AppBar (SliverAppBar with collapsing header)
78	│   ├── Leading: Back button (48pt touch target)
79	│   ├── Title: Article topic text (centered or trailing)
80	│   └── Actions: Bookmark icon, Share icon
81	├── Body: SingleChildScrollView
82	│   ├── SliverAppBar with FlexibleSpace (hero image, collapses on scroll)
83	│   └── Remaining content (ArticleHeader, ArticleBody, RelatedArticles)
84	└── No BottomNavigationBar, No FAB
85	```
86	
87	### AppBar Behavior
88	- Collapsing header: `SliverAppBar` with `flexibleSpace` containing the hero image
89	- Background: transparent, blends into scaffold `Lavender Tint`
90	- On scroll: image collapses and fades; title transitions from large to compact
91	- Back button: standard leading, returns to Education or previous screen
92	- Trailing actions: bookmark (toggleable), share (system sheet)
93	
94	### Navigation Bar
95	- Hidden (not visible during article reading)
96	- Swipe-back enabled for dismissal
97	
98	### Screen Padding
99	- Horizontal: 16dp from each edge
100	- Vertical sections: 24dp between major sections
101	- Card internal padding: 16dp
102	
103	## 7. Sections
104	
105	### 7.1 Article Header (collapsed view in SliverAppBar)
106	
107	**Description:** Full-width hero image at top, topic badge, article title, and metadata. When scrolled, this collapses into a compact AppBar representation.
108	
109	**Widget:** `SliverAppBar` with `flexibleSpace` containing a `Column`
110	- Hero image: `BoxFit.cover`, height 240dp expanded / 56dp collapsed
111	- Topic badge: `Container` with `Blush Rose` background, white text, pill shape (12dp radius)
112	- Title: `Text` with `Section Header` style, max 3 lines, ellipsis overflow
113	- Metadata row: Author name, date, estimated read time (separated by `•`)
114	
115	**Data requirements:**
116	```
117	Article {
118	  id: String
119	  title: String
120	  topic: String (e.g., "Nutrition", "Body Changes")
121	  imageUrl: String (hero image URL)
122	  authorName: String
123	  publishedDate: DateTime
124	  readTimeMinutes: int
125	}
126	```
127	
128	**Interactive elements:**
129	- Hero image: shared element transition (hero) from EducationScreen article card
130	- Scroll: collapses header, triggers AppBar fade-in
131	
132	---
133	
134	### 7.2 Article Body
135	
136	**Description:** Formatted text content with section headers and pull-quote styling.
137	
138	**Widget:** `SingleChildScrollView` → `Padding` → `Column`
139	- Section headers: `Text` with `Title Medium` style, `Lavender Bloom` color
140	- Body paragraphs: `Text` with `Body` style, `Deep Graphite` color, `0.15` letter spacing
141	- Pull quotes: `Container` with `Blush Rose` left border (4dp), italic text, 16dp padding
142	- Bullet lists: `Row` with `Blush Rose` dot + body text
143	
144	**Data requirements:**
145	```
146	Article {
147	  sections: List<ArticleSection>
148	}
149	
150	ArticleSection {
151	  type: enum (paragraph, header, pullquote, list)
152	  content: String
153	  items: List<String>? // for list type
154	}
155	```
156	
157	**Interactive elements:**
158	- None (read-only content)
159	- Links in future: open external browser
160	
161	---
162	
163	### 7.3 Related Articles
164	
165	**Description:** Bottom section displaying 2–3 related article cards in a horizontal `ListView`.
166	
167	**Widget:** `Column` with section title and horizontal `ListView`
168	- Section title: `Text` "Related Articles" with `Title Medium` style
169	- Related article cards: `InkWell` with `ArticleCard` widget (120dp width, image + title)
170	- Card spacing: 12dp between cards
171	- Tap → navigate to new `ArticleReaderScreen` with hero transition
172	
173	**Data requirements:**
174	```
175	Article {
176	  relatedArticleIds: List<String>
177	}
178	
179	ArticleProvider.getArticlesByIds(List<String>) → List<Article>
180	```
181	
182	**Interactive elements:**
183	- Tap card: push new `ArticleReaderScreen` with that article's ID
184	- Hero transition: article card image and title animate to new screen header
185	
186	---
187	
188	### 7.4 Bookmark Action
189	
190	**Description:** Trailing AppBar icon that toggles article bookmark state.
191	
192	**Widget:** `IconButton` in AppBar actions
193	- Unbookmarked: `Icons.bookmark_outline` (Stone Grey)
194	- Bookmarked: `Icons.bookmark` (Lavender Bloom, filled)
195	
196	**Data requirements:**
197	```
198	Article.isBookmarked: bool
199	ArticleProvider.toggleBookmark(String articleId)
200	```
201	
202	**Interactive elements:**
203	- Tap: toggle bookmark state, animate icon with 150ms scale bounce + color transition
204	- State persists in `ArticleProvider`
205	
206	---
207	
208	### 7.5 Share Action
209	
210	**Description:** Trailing AppBar icon that opens system share sheet.
211	
212	**Widget:** `IconButton` in AppBar actions
213	- Icon: `Icons.share_outlined` (Stone Grey)
214	- Tap → `Share.share(articleUrl, subject: articleTitle)` from `share_plus`
215	
216	**Data requirements:**
217	```
218	Article {
219	  shareUrl: String
220	  title: String
221	}
222	```
223	
224	**Interactive elements:**
225	- Tap: open native share sheet with article title and URL
226	
227	## 8. Data
228	
229	### Article Entity
230	```
231	Article {
232	  id: String (unique identifier)
233	  title: String (article headline)
234	  topic: String (e.g., "Nutrition", "Body Changes", "Exercise", "Mental Health")
235	  imageUrl: String (hero image URL)
236	  authorName: String
237	  publishedDate: DateTime
238	  readTimeMinutes: int
239	  content: List<ArticleSection>
240	  relatedArticleIds: List<String>
241	  isBookmarked: bool
242	  shareUrl: String
243	}
244	
245	ArticleSection {
246	  type: ArticleSectionType (paragraph, header, pullquote, list)
247	  content: String
248	  items: List<String>? (for list type)
249	}
250	```
251	
252	### Provider: `ArticleProvider`
253	- `getArticle(String id)`: returns `Article?`
254	- `getRelatedArticles(List<String> ids)`: returns `List<Article>`
255	- `toggleBookmark(String id)`: flips `isBookmarked` state
256	- State: in-memory for MVP (persisted to local storage in future)
257	
258	## 9. Motion
259	
260	### Page Transition
261	- Type: push with 300ms slide + fade
262	- Curve: `Curves.easeInOut`
263	- Back swipe: enabled, reverses the animation
264	
265	### Hero Transition (from Education Screen)
266	- Duration: 350ms
267	- Easing: fast-out-slow-in (`Curves.easeOut` enter, `Curves.easeIn` exit)
268	- Shared elements: hero image, article title text
269	- Trigger: tap article card in EducationScreen → article reader opens
270	
271	### Header Collapse (SliverAppBar)
272	- Behavior: scroll down → header shrinks, image fades
273	- Animation: tied to scroll position, continuous
274	- Title: transitions from large (22pt) to compact (16pt) as AppBar collapses
275	
276	### Bookmark Toggle
277	- Duration: 150ms
278	- Effect: scale 1.0 → 1.2 → 1.0 + color fade from outline to filled
279	- Curve: `Curves.easeOut`
280	
281	### Card Tap (Related Articles)
282	- Duration: 200ms
283	- Effect: scale to 98% on press, return to 100%
284	- Curve: `Curves.easeOut`
285	
286	## 10. Accessibility
287	
288	### Semantic Labels
289	- Back button: "Navigate back"
290	- Bookmark icon (unbookmarked): "Bookmark article"
291	- Bookmark icon (bookmarked): "Remove bookmark"
292	- Share icon: "Share article"
293	- Related article card: "Read [article title]"
294	- Hero image: "Article hero image"
295	
296	### Focus Order
297	1. Back button (leading)
298	2. Bookmark action
299	3. Share action
300	4. Article body content (scrollable)
301	5. Related article cards (traversed in order)
302	
303	### Contrast Ratios
304	- Body text (`#1F2937` on `#FAFAFA`): 14.7:1 ✓ (exceeds 7:1)
305	- Secondary text (`#6B7280` on `#FAFAFA`): 4.6:1 ✓ (exceeds 4.5:1)
306	- Topic badge (white on `#F9A8D4`): 3.2:1 ✓ (exceeds 3:1)
307	- AppBar title (`#1F2937` on `#F5F3FF`): 12.6:1 ✓ (exceeds 7:1)
308	
309	### Touch Targets
310	- All interactive elements: minimum 48dp × 48dp
311	- AppBar icons: 48dp touch target via `IconButton`
312	- Related article cards: full card is tappable
313	
314	### Screen Reader
315	- Article title announced when screen loads
316	- Section headers announced as navigation landmarks
317	- Pull quotes read with emphasis
318	
319	## 11. Anti-Patterns
320	
321	**Do NOT:**
322	- Use `AppBar` with `title` instead of `SliverAppBar` with collapsing header
323	- Show `BottomNavigationBar` (hidden for reading focus)
324	- Use pure black (`#000000`) or pure white (`#FFFFFF`) for text
325	- Apply hard shadows or aggressive elevation
326	- Use Inter, Roboto, or non-Nunito fonts
327	- Display more than 3 related articles (overwhelming)
328	- Use unsourced placeholder images
329	- Allow body text smaller than 16sp
330	- Use arbitrary spacing not aligned to 8pt grid
331	- Trigger animations longer than 400ms (jarring)
332	- Use `ListView` for article body (performance on long articles)
[2026-05-19T02:18:49.393Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_b2s927ss46mr_3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Pregnant Tracker - Baby Bump — Design System\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Visual Theme\n4\t\n5\t**Theme Name:** Gentle Bloom\n6\t\n7\t**Mood:** A soft, nurturing sanctuary — warm natural light filtering through a nursery window, reassuring and calm without being clinical or sterile.\n8\t\n9\t**Light Mode (Primary):** Light mode is the primary experience. The interface feels like morning sunlight in a cozy, plant-filled nursery — airy, warm, and welcoming.\n10\t\n11\t**Dark Mode (Secondary):** Deep twilight tones that maintain the warmth of the light palette. Not cold charcoal — more like a softly lit nursery at dusk with warm accent lighting.\n12\t\n13\t**Key Visual Metaphors:** Organic shapes and rounded corners evoke softness and approachability. Breathing room between elements mirrors the intentional calm the app encourages. No sharp edges or sterile clinical aesthetics.\n14\t\n15\t---\n16\t\n17\t## 2. Color Palette\n18\t\n19\t### Light Theme\n20\t\n21\t- **Lavender Bloom** (#7C3AED) — Primary brand color, used for key actions, navigation highlights, and the primary AppBar. Provides confident yet gentle presence.\n22\t- **Blush Rose** (#F9A8D4) — Secondary accent, used for mood emojis, mood trend highlights, and decorative touches that feel warm and nurturing.\n23\t- **Soft Mint** (#6EE7B7) — Tertiary color for success states, checkmarks, and positive confirmations. Subtle and reassuring.\n24\t- **Morning Mist** (#FAFAFA) — Card and surface backgrounds. Clean without being stark white.\n25\t- **Lavender Tint** (#F5F3FF) — Scaffold background. A gentle purple-tinted wash that unifies the visual experience.\n26\t- **Deep Graphite** (#1F2937) — Primary text color. Softer than pure black, easier on the eyes during extended reading.\n27\t- **Stone Grey** (#6B7280) — Secondary text, captions, timestamps, and supporting labels.\n28\t- **Misty Border** (#E5E7EB) — Borders, dividers, and subtle structural lines. Barely-there structure.\n29\t- **Soft Coral** (#EF4444) — Error states, validation messages, destructive actions. Stands out without alarm.\n30\t- **Warm White** (#FFFFFF) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces.\n31\t\n32\t### Dark Theme\n33\t\n34\t- **Twilight Bloom** (#9F67FF) — Primary brand in dark mode. Slightly lighter and warmer than the light primary to maintain softness in low-light conditions.\n35\t- **Dusky Rose** (#FBC4E0) — Secondary accent for dark mode. Warmer and more luminous than the light secondary.\n36\t- **Night Mint** (#34D399) — Tertiary success color for dark mode. More vibrant to stand out against dark surfaces.\n37\t- **Deep Twilight** (#1E1B2E) — Card and surface backgrounds in dark mode. Warm-tinted dark purple-grey, never cold.\n38\t- **Night Sky** (#13111C) — Scaffold background in dark mode. Deep but warm, avoiding pure black.\n39\t- **Soft Pearl** (#F3F4F6) — Primary text in dark mode. High contrast but not harsh.\n40\t- **Muted Silver** (#9CA3AF) — Secondary text, captions, and supporting labels in dark mode.\n41\t- **Deep Border** (#2D2B3A) — Borders, dividers, and structural lines in dark mode. Subtle but visible.\n42\t- **Muted Coral** (#F87171) — Error states in dark mode. Slightly softer red to maintain the warm tone.\n43\t- **Charcoal Surface** (#252336) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces in dark mode.\n44\t\n45\t### Neutral Scale (Light Theme)\n46\t- **Ivory** (#FAFAF9)\n47\t- **Pearl** (#F5F5F4)\n48\t- **Stone 100** (#F5F5F4)\n49\t- **Stone 200** (#E7E5E4)\n50\t- **Stone 300** (#D6D3D1)\n51\t- **Stone 400** (#A8A29E)\n52\t- **Stone 500** (#78716C)\n53\t- **Stone 600** (#57534E)\n54\t- **Stone 700** (#44403C)\n55\t- **Stone 800** (#292524)\n56\t- **Stone 900** (#1C1917)\n57\t\n58\t### Neutral Scale (Dark Theme)\n59\t- **Night Ivory** (#1A1825)\n60\t- **Night Pearl** (#252336)\n61\t- **Night Stone 100** (#2D2B3A)\n62\t- **Night Stone 200** (#3D3A4D)\n63\t- **Night Stone 300** (#4D4A5E)\n64\t- **Night Stone 400** (#6B6880)\n65\t- **Night Stone 500** (#8B8899)\n66\t- **Night Stone 600** (#ABABB9)\n67\t- **Night Stone 700** (#CBCAD0)\n68\t- **Night Stone 800** (#E5E4E8)\n69\t- **Night Stone 900** (#F3F4F6)\n70\t\n71\t---\n72\t\n73\t## 3. Typography\n74\t\n75\t### Font Selection\n76\t\n77\t- **Display Font:** Nunito — Rounded, friendly letterforms with a warm, approachable character. Excellent for headlines and large text where softness and readability are paramount. Nunito's terminals and joints have a gentle, open quality that avoids feeling sharp or clinical. Used for: Hero display, screen titles, section headers.\n78\t\n79\t- **Body Font:** Nunito — The same family is used for body text to maintain visual cohesion. At reading sizes, Nunito's proportions provide comfortable extended reading without fatigue. Used for: Body text, labels, captions, button text, chips.\n80\t\n81\t### Type Scale\n82\t\n83\t| Role | Font | Weight | Size | Line Height | Usage |\n84\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n85\t| Hero display | Nunito | Bold (700) | 57pt | 64pt | Splash screens, week number display on pregnancy hero |\n86\t| Screen title | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 28pt | 36pt | Top-level screen headings |\n87\t| Section header | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 22pt | 28pt | Card titles, section headers within screens |\n88\t| Subtitle | Nunito | Medium (500) | 16pt | 24pt | List item titles, subtitles, chart labels |\n89\t| Body | Nunito | Regular (400) | 16pt | 24pt | Primary reading text, article body |\n90\t| Body small | Nunito | Regular (400) | 14pt | 20pt | Secondary text, descriptions, log entry details |\n91\t| Button label | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 14pt | 20pt | Button text, chip labels, navigation items |\n92\t| Caption | Nunito | Medium (500) | 11pt | 16pt | Badges, timestamps, tab labels, small metadata |\n93\t\n94\t### Letter Spacing Guidelines\n95\t\n96\t- Hero display: 0pt (set solid)\n97\t- Screen titles: -0.5pt (slight tightening for large type)\n98\t- Body text: 0.15pt (open, readable spacing)\n99\t- Caption and labels: 0.4pt (clear separation for small text)\n100\t\n101\t---\n102\t\n103\t## 4. Component Styles\n104\t\n105\t### Card\n106\t- **Corner radius:** 16 points\n107\t- **Shadow depth:** Soft, diffused shadow — 8 points blur, 2 points offset-y, rgba(0,0,0,0.08) in light mode; rgba(0,0,0,0.25) in dark mode. The shadow feels like gentle morning light creating a soft pool beneath the card.\n108\t- **Background:** Morning Mist (#FAFAFA) in light mode; Deep Twilight (#1E1B2E) in dark mode\n109\t- **Internal padding:** 16 points all sides; 20 points for cards containing action buttons\n110\t- **Tap feedback:** Subtle scale-down to 98% on press, with 200ms ease-out return. The press feels like a gentle press into a soft surface rather than a click.\n111\t- **Spacing between cards:** 12 points\n112\t\n113\t### Buttons\n114\t\n115\t**Primary Button**\n116\t- Shape: Pill-shaped (fully rounded on all corners, corner radius equals half the button height)\n117\t- Minimum height: 48 points (touch target compliance)\n118\t- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n119\t- Text: White (#FFFFFF), SemiBold, 14pt\n120\t- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background darkens by 8% brightness\n121\t- Corner radius: 24 points (fully rounded pill)\n122\t\n123\t**Secondary Button**\n124\t- Shape: Pill-shaped\n125\t- Minimum height: 48 points\n126\t- Background: Transparent with Lavender Bloom border (2 points stroke) in light mode; Transparent with Twilight Bloom border in dark mode\n127\t- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n128\t- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background fills with 10% primary color\n129\t- Corner radius: 24 points\n130\t\n131\t**Text Button**\n132\t- Shape: No background, no border\n133\t- Minimum height: 48 points\n134\t- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Text button inherits no background, only color\n135\t- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out opacity reduction to 60%\n136\t\n137\t**FAB (Floating Action Button)**\n138\t- Size: 56 points diameter\n139\t- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED); Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n140\t- Icon: White, 24 points\n141\t- Shadow: Medium diffused shadow, 12 points blur\n142\t- Press feedback: 200ms scale to 90%, shadow intensifies slightly\n143\t\n144\t### Text Input\n145\t- **Decoration style:** Filled background — a rounded container that feels like a gentle trough for text\n146\t- **Corner radius:** 12 points\n147\t- **Fill color:** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n148\t- **Border:** None at rest; on focus, a 2-point Lavender Bloom border appears with smooth 200ms transition\n149\t- **Label behavior:** Floating label that rises above the field on focus or when content is present; label color transitions from Stone 400 (#A8A29E) to Lavender Bloom on focus\n150\t- **Error state:** Border becomes Soft Coral (#EF4444), error message appears below in Soft Coral, 14pt\n151\t- **Minimum height:** 56 points to ensure comfortable touch interaction\n152\t\n153\t### Chip\n154\t- **Shape:** Fully rounded pill (corner radius = half the chip height)\n155\t- **Corner radius:** 16 points (pill shape)\n156\t- **Background (default):** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n157\t- **Background (selected):** Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity (#7C3AED1A), with Lavender Bloom text\n158\t- **Minimum height:** 32 points (comfortable touch target)\n159\t- **Horizontal padding:** 12 points left and right\n160\t- **Tap feedback:** 150ms opacity shift to selected state, no scale change (chips feel like gentle toggles, not buttons)\n161\t\n162\t### Bottom Sheet\n163\t- **Top corner radius:** 28 points — large, prominent rounding that feels organic and soft\n164\t- **Background:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n165\t- **Handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered at top, Stone 300 (#D6D3D1) color in light mode; Night Stone 200 in dark mode. The handle feels like a gentle grip point, not structural.\n166\t- **Maximum height:** 90% of screen height for full sheets; 50% for half sheets\n167\t- **Shadow:** Soft diffused shadow, 16 points blur, 4 points offset-y\n168\t- **Open animation:** 250ms smooth deceleration — slides up from bottom edge with subtle fade\n169\t\n170\t### Navigation Bar (Bottom Tabs)\n171\t- **Background color:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n172\t- **Active indicator:** A small rounded pill beneath the active tab icon and label. The pill is filled with Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity. The indicator transitions smoothly (200ms) between tabs.\n173\t- **Icon style:** Outlined icons for inactive state, filled icons for active state — the active tab is visually \"filled\" with color\n174\t- **Icon size:** 24 points\n175\t- **Label visibility:** Labels are always visible below icons — no hidden label behavior. Text is SemiBold 11pt when active, Regular 11pt when inactive.\n176\t- **Touch target:** Each tab item has a minimum 48-point touch target height\n177\t- **Safe area:** Bottom navigation respects the home indicator area on notched devices\n178\t\n179\t### App Bar\n180\t- **Background:** Transparent to scaffold background color (Lavender Tint #F5F3FF in light mode; Night Sky #13111C in dark mode). The AppBar feels like it floats over the content.\n181\t- **Title text style:** SemiBold 20pt, Deep Graphite (#1F2937) in light mode; Soft Pearl (#F3F4F6) in dark mode\n182\t- **Scroll behavior:** On scrollable content, the AppBar has a subtle fade-in effect as content scrolls beneath it. On screens with SliverAppBar, the AppBar collapses to show a smaller representation.\n183\t- **Leading/back button:** Icon button with 48-point touch target, Lavender Bloom on tap\n184\t\n185\t---\n186\t\n187\t## 5. Layout Principles\n188\t\n189\t- **Base spacing unit:** 8 points — all spacing is derived from multiples of 8\n190\t- **Screen horizontal padding:** 16 points from each edge\n191\t- **Section vertical spacing:** 24 points between major sections\n192\t- **Card internal padding:** 16 points all sides\n193\t- **Card gap:** 12 points between cards in a grid or list\n194\t- **List item minimum height:** 56 points (comfortable touch target for interactive list items)\n195\t- **Minimum touch target:** 48 points (compliant with mobile accessibility standards)\n196\t- **Bottom sheet handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered 20 points from top\n197\t- **Safe area awareness:** Respect status bar at top (add 12 points padding when status bar is visible) and home indicator at bottom (bottom navigation and FAB account for this)\n198\t- **Grid gutters:** 12 points between columns in 2-column grids\n199\t- **Card corner radius:** 16 points for standard cards; 12 points for smaller card variants\n200\t\n201\t---\n202\t\n203\t## 6. Motion & Animation\n204\t\n205\tMotion is gentle, purposeful, and never jarring. The app feels like a calm, flowing experience rather than a reactive, mechanical one.\n206\t\n207\t- **Page transitions:** 300ms duration, smooth deceleration. Screen content slides and fades simultaneously — the new screen appears to gently settle into place.\n208\t- **Micro-interactions:** 200ms duration, snappy ease-out. Button presses, chip selections, toggle switches — responses feel quick but soft, like a gentle tap on a responsive surface.\n209\t- **Hero transitions:** 350ms duration, fast-out-slow-in easing. When navigating from a list to a detail view (e.g., article reader), shared elements like images and titles smoothly expand and continue their motion arc.\n210\t- **Staggered list reveals:** 50ms delay between each item. When content loads, list items cascade into view in a waterfall — items appear 50ms apart, creating a sense of gentle unfolding rather than a sudden dump of content.\n211\t- **Bottom sheets:** 250ms duration, smooth deceleration. Sheets slide up from the bottom edge, decelerating naturally as they reach their resting position.\n212\t- **Pull-to-refresh:** 150ms duration, quick snap. The refresh indicator appears and dismisses quickly but not abruptly.\n213\t- **Tab indicator movement:** 200ms duration, ease-in-out. The active indicator pill smoothly glides between tab positions.\n214\t- **Card tap feedback:** 200ms ease-out scale to 98%, then 200ms ease-out return to 100%.\n215\t- **FAB appearance:** 200ms fade-in with subtle scale from 95% to 100%.\n216\t\n217\t---\n218\t\n219\t## 7. Anti-Patterns (Banned Design Rules)\n220\t\n221\t- No default platform colors — every color comes from the design system palette\n222\t- No ad-hoc text sizing — all text uses the defined type scale\n223\t- No inconsistent spacing — all spacing uses the 8-point base unit scale\n224\t- No arbitrary elevation — every shadow level communicates a specific hierarchy\n225\t- No Inter or Roboto — Nunito is the only font family\n226\t- No purple or neon AI aesthetic — colors are warm pastels, not synthetic\n227\t- No generic gradients — backgrounds are flat or subtly tinted, not gradient-washed\n228\t- No shadows without purpose — elevation always communicates hierarchy\n229\t- No desktop patterns — no sidebars, hover tooltips, right-click menus, or desktop-only interaction patterns\n230\t- No touch targets smaller than 48 points\n231\t- No critical actions outside the thumb zone (bottom two-thirds of screen height)\n232\t- No pure black (#000000) anywhere — deep charcoal and off-black only\n233\t- No pure white (#FFFFFF) for text — use off-white tones that reduce eye strain"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f062649-0c01-450d-a85b-f7569af9b4e9","uuid":"b961f1c0-afef-4455-a7c0-49fb240bf404","timestamp":"2026-05-19T02:18:49.392Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/minh/Documents/openplayboosks/examples/baby-app/.stitch/system/DESIGN.md","content":"# Pregnant Tracker - Baby Bump — Design System\n\n## 1. Visual Theme\n\n**Theme Name:** Gentle Bloom\n\n**Mood:** A soft, nurturing sanctuary — warm natural light filtering through a nursery window, reassuring and calm without being clinical or sterile.\n\n**Light Mode (Primary):** Light mode is the primary experience. The interface feels like morning sunlight in a cozy, plant-filled nursery — airy, warm, and welcoming.\n\n**Dark Mode (Secondary):** Deep twilight tones that maintain the warmth of the light palette. Not cold charcoal — more like a softly lit nursery at dusk with warm accent lighting.\n\n**Key Visual Metaphors:** Organic shapes and rounded corners evoke softness and approachability. Breathing room between elements mirrors the intentional calm the app encourages. No sharp edges or sterile clinical aesthetics.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Color Palette\n\n### Light Theme\n\n- **Lavender Bloom** (#7C3AED) — Primary brand color, used for key actions, navigation highlights, and the primary AppBar. Provides confident yet gentle presence.\n- **Blush Rose** (#F9A8D4) — Secondary accent, used for mood emojis, mood trend highlights, and decorative touches that feel warm and nurturing.\n- **Soft Mint** (#6EE7B7) — Tertiary color for success states, checkmarks, and positive confirmations. Subtle and reassuring.\n- **Morning Mist** (#FAFAFA) — Card and surface backgrounds. Clean without being stark white.\n- **Lavender Tint** (#F5F3FF) — Scaffold background. A gentle purple-tinted wash that unifies the visual experience.\n- **Deep Graphite** (#1F2937) — Primary text color. Softer than pure black, easier on the eyes during extended reading.\n- **Stone Grey** (#6B7280) — Secondary text, captions, timestamps, and supporting labels.\n- **Misty Border** (#E5E7EB) — Borders, dividers, and subtle structural lines. Barely-there structure.\n- **Soft Coral** (#EF4444) — Error states, validation messages, destructive actions. Stands out without alarm.\n- **Warm White** (#FFFFFF) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces.\n\n### Dark Theme\n\n- **Twilight Bloom** (#9F67FF) — Primary brand in dark mode. Slightly lighter and warmer than the light primary to maintain softness in low-light conditions.\n- **Dusky Rose** (#FBC4E0) — Secondary accent for dark mode. Warmer and more luminous than the light secondary.\n- **Night Mint** (#34D399) — Tertiary success color for dark mode. More vibrant to stand out against dark surfaces.\n- **Deep Twilight** (#1E1B2E) — Card and surface backgrounds in dark mode. Warm-tinted dark purple-grey, never cold.\n- **Night Sky** (#13111C) — Scaffold background in dark mode. Deep but warm, avoiding pure black.\n- **Soft Pearl** (#F3F4F6) — Primary text in dark mode. High contrast but not harsh.\n- **Muted Silver** (#9CA3AF) — Secondary text, captions, and supporting labels in dark mode.\n- **Deep Border** (#2D2B3A) — Borders, dividers, and structural lines in dark mode. Subtle but visible.\n- **Muted Coral** (#F87171) — Error states in dark mode. Slightly softer red to maintain the warm tone.\n- **Charcoal Surface** (#252336) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces in dark mode.\n\n### Neutral Scale (Light Theme)\n- **Ivory** (#FAFAF9)\n- **Pearl** (#F5F5F4)\n- **Stone 100** (#F5F5F4)\n- **Stone 200** (#E7E5E4)\n- **Stone 300** (#D6D3D1)\n- **Stone 400** (#A8A29E)\n- **Stone 500** (#78716C)\n- **Stone 600** (#57534E)\n- **Stone 700** (#44403C)\n- **Stone 800** (#292524)\n- **Stone 900** (#1C1917)\n\n### Neutral Scale (Dark Theme)\n- **Night Ivory** (#1A1825)\n- **Night Pearl** (#252336)\n- **Night Stone 100** (#2D2B3A)\n- **Night Stone 200** (#3D3A4D)\n- **Night Stone 300** (#4D4A5E)\n- **Night Stone 400** (#6B6880)\n- **Night Stone 500** (#8B8899)\n- **Night Stone 600** (#ABABB9)\n- **Night Stone 700** (#CBCAD0)\n- **Night Stone 800** (#E5E4E8)\n- **Night Stone 900** (#F3F4F6)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Typography\n\n### Font Selection\n\n- **Display Font:** Nunito — Rounded, friendly letterforms with a warm, approachable character. Excellent for headlines and large text where softness and readability are paramount. Nunito's terminals and joints have a gentle, open quality that avoids feeling sharp or clinical. Used for: Hero display, screen titles, section headers.\n\n- **Body Font:** Nunito — The same family is used for body text to maintain visual cohesion. At reading sizes, Nunito's proportions provide comfortable extended reading without fatigue. Used for: Body text, labels, captions, button text, chips.\n\n### Type Scale\n\n| Role | Font | Weight | Size | Line Height | Usage |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Hero display | Nunito | Bold (700) | 57pt | 64pt | Splash screens, week number display on pregnancy hero |\n| Screen title | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 28pt | 36pt | Top-level screen headings |\n| Section header | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 22pt | 28pt | Card titles, section headers within screens |\n| Subtitle | Nunito | Medium (500) | 16pt | 24pt | List item titles, subtitles, chart labels |\n| Body | Nunito | Regular (400) | 16pt | 24pt | Primary reading text, article body |\n| Body small | Nunito | Regular (400) | 14pt | 20pt | Secondary text, descriptions, log entry details |\n| Button label | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 14pt | 20pt | Button text, chip labels, navigation items |\n| Caption | Nunito | Medium (500) | 11pt | 16pt | Badges, timestamps, tab labels, small metadata |\n\n### Letter Spacing Guidelines\n\n- Hero display: 0pt (set solid)\n- Screen titles: -0.5pt (slight tightening for large type)\n- Body text: 0.15pt (open, readable spacing)\n- Caption and labels: 0.4pt (clear separation for small text)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Component Styles\n\n### Card\n- **Corner radius:** 16 points\n- **Shadow depth:** Soft, diffused shadow — 8 points blur, 2 points offset-y, rgba(0,0,0,0.08) in light mode; rgba(0,0,0,0.25) in dark mode. The shadow feels like gentle morning light creating a soft pool beneath the card.\n- **Background:** Morning Mist (#FAFAFA) in light mode; Deep Twilight (#1E1B2E) in dark mode\n- **Internal padding:** 16 points all sides; 20 points for cards containing action buttons\n- **Tap feedback:** Subtle scale-down to 98% on press, with 200ms ease-out return. The press feels like a gentle press into a soft surface rather than a click.\n- **Spacing between cards:** 12 points\n\n### Buttons\n\n**Primary Button**\n- Shape: Pill-shaped (fully rounded on all corners, corner radius equals half the button height)\n- Minimum height: 48 points (touch target compliance)\n- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n- Text: White (#FFFFFF), SemiBold, 14pt\n- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background darkens by 8% brightness\n- Corner radius: 24 points (fully rounded pill)\n\n**Secondary Button**\n- Shape: Pill-shaped\n- Minimum height: 48 points\n- Background: Transparent with Lavender Bloom border (2 points stroke) in light mode; Transparent with Twilight Bloom border in dark mode\n- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background fills with 10% primary color\n- Corner radius: 24 points\n\n**Text Button**\n- Shape: No background, no border\n- Minimum height: 48 points\n- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Text button inherits no background, only color\n- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out opacity reduction to 60%\n\n**FAB (Floating Action Button)**\n- Size: 56 points diameter\n- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED); Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n- Icon: White, 24 points\n- Shadow: Medium diffused shadow, 12 points blur\n- Press feedback: 200ms scale to 90%, shadow intensifies slightly\n\n### Text Input\n- **Decoration style:** Filled background — a rounded container that feels like a gentle trough for text\n- **Corner radius:** 12 points\n- **Fill color:** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n- **Border:** None at rest; on focus, a 2-point Lavender Bloom border appears with smooth 200ms transition\n- **Label behavior:** Floating label that rises above the field on focus or when content is present; label color transitions from Stone 400 (#A8A29E) to Lavender Bloom on focus\n- **Error state:** Border becomes Soft Coral (#EF4444), error message appears below in Soft Coral, 14pt\n- **Minimum height:** 56 points to ensure comfortable touch interaction\n\n### Chip\n- **Shape:** Fully rounded pill (corner radius = half the chip height)\n- **Corner radius:** 16 points (pill shape)\n- **Background (default):** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n- **Background (selected):** Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity (#7C3AED1A), with Lavender Bloom text\n- **Minimum height:** 32 points (comfortable touch target)\n- **Horizontal padding:** 12 points left and right\n- **Tap feedback:** 150ms opacity shift to selected state, no scale change (chips feel like gentle toggles, not buttons)\n\n### Bottom Sheet\n- **Top corner radius:** 28 points — large, prominent rounding that feels organic and soft\n- **Background:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n- **Handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered at top, Stone 300 (#D6D3D1) color in light mode; Night Stone 200 in dark mode. The handle feels like a gentle grip point, not structural.\n- **Maximum height:** 90% of screen height for full sheets; 50% for half sheets\n- **Shadow:** Soft diffused shadow, 16 points blur, 4 points offset-y\n- **Open animation:** 250ms smooth deceleration — slides up from bottom edge with subtle fade\n\n### Navigation Bar (Bottom Tabs)\n- **Background color:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n- **Active indicator:** A small rounded pill beneath the active tab icon and label. The pill is filled with Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity. The indicator transitions smoothly (200ms) between tabs.\n- **Icon style:** Outlined icons for inactive state, filled icons for active state — the active tab is visually \"filled\" with color\n- **Icon size:** 24 points\n- **Label visibility:** Labels are always visible below icons — no hidden label behavior. Text is SemiBold 11pt when active, Regular 11pt when inactive.\n- **Touch target:** Each tab item has a minimum 48-point touch target height\n- **Safe area:** Bottom navigation respects the home indicator area on notched devices\n\n### App Bar\n- **Background:** Transparent to scaffold background color (Lavender Tint #F5F3FF in light mode; Night Sky #13111C in dark mode). The AppBar feels like it floats over the content.\n- **Title text style:** SemiBold 20pt, Deep Graphite (#1F2937) in light mode; Soft Pearl (#F3F4F6) in dark mode\n- **Scroll behavior:** On scrollable content, the AppBar has a subtle fade-in effect as content scrolls beneath it. On screens with SliverAppBar, the AppBar collapses to show a smaller representation.\n- **Leading/back button:** Icon button with 48-point touch target, Lavender Bloom on tap\n\n---\n\n## 5. Layout Principles\n\n- **Base spacing unit:** 8 points — all spacing is derived from multiples of 8\n- **Screen horizontal padding:** 16 points from each edge\n- **Section vertical spacing:** 24 points between major sections\n- **Card internal padding:** 16 points all sides\n- **Card gap:** 12 points between cards in a grid or list\n- **List item minimum height:** 56 points (comfortable touch target for interactive list items)\n- **Minimum touch target:** 48 points (compliant with mobile accessibility standards)\n- **Bottom sheet handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered 20 points from top\n- **Safe area awareness:** Respect status bar at top (add 12 points padding when status bar is visible) and home indicator at bottom (bottom navigation and FAB account for this)\n- **Grid gutters:** 12 points between columns in 2-column grids\n- **Card corner radius:** 16 points for standard cards; 12 points for smaller card variants\n\n---\n\n## 6. Motion & Animation\n\nMotion is gentle, purposeful, and never jarring. The app feels like a calm, flowing experience rather than a reactive, mechanical one.\n\n- **Page transitions:** 300ms duration, smooth deceleration. Screen content slides and fades simultaneously — the new screen appears to gently settle into place.\n- **Micro-interactions:** 200ms duration, snappy ease-out. Button presses, chip selections, toggle switches — responses feel quick but soft, like a gentle tap on a responsive surface.\n- **Hero transitions:** 350ms duration, fast-out-slow-in easing. When navigating from a list to a detail view (e.g., article reader), shared elements like images and titles smoothly expand and continue their motion arc.\n- **Staggered list reveals:** 50ms delay between each item. When content loads, list items cascade into view in a waterfall — items appear 50ms apart, creating a sense of gentle unfolding rather than a sudden dump of content.\n- **Bottom sheets:** 250ms duration, smooth deceleration. Sheets slide up from the bottom edge, decelerating naturally as they reach their resting position.\n- **Pull-to-refresh:** 150ms duration, quick snap. The refresh indicator appears and dismisses quickly but not abruptly.\n- **Tab indicator movement:** 200ms duration, ease-in-out. The active indicator pill smoothly glides between tab positions.\n- **Card tap feedback:** 200ms ease-out scale to 98%, then 200ms ease-out return to 100%.\n- **FAB appearance:** 200ms fade-in with subtle scale from 95% to 100%.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Anti-Patterns (Banned Design Rules)\n\n- No default platform colors — every color comes from the design system palette\n- No ad-hoc text sizing — all text uses the defined type scale\n- No inconsistent spacing — all spacing uses the 8-point base unit scale\n- No arbitrary elevation — every shadow level communicates a specific hierarchy\n- No Inter or Roboto — Nunito is the only font family\n- No purple or neon AI aesthetic — colors are warm pastels, not synthetic\n- No generic gradients — backgrounds are flat or subtly tinted, not gradient-washed\n- No shadows without purpose — elevation always communicates hierarchy\n- No desktop patterns — no sidebars, hover tooltips, right-click menus, or desktop-only interaction patterns\n- No touch targets smaller than 48 points\n- No critical actions outside the thumb zone (bottom two-thirds of screen height)\n- No pure black (#000000) anywhere — deep charcoal and off-black only\n- No pure white (#FFFFFF) for text — use off-white tones that reduce eye strain","numLines":233,"startLine":1,"totalLines":233}}}
[2026-05-19T02:18:49.393Z] [STREAM_EVENT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_b2s927ss46mr_3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Pregnant Tracker - Baby Bump — Design System\n2\t\n3\t## 1. Visual Theme\n4\t\n5\t**Theme Name:** Gentle Bloom\n6\t\n7\t**Mood:** A soft, nurturing sanctuary — warm natural light filtering through a nursery window, reassuring and calm without being clinical or sterile.\n8\t\n9\t**Light Mode (Primary):** Light mode is the primary experience. The interface feels like morning sunlight in a cozy, plant-filled nursery — airy, warm, and welcoming.\n10\t\n11\t**Dark Mode (Secondary):** Deep twilight tones that maintain the warmth of the light palette. Not cold charcoal — more like a softly lit nursery at dusk with warm accent lighting.\n12\t\n13\t**Key Visual Metaphors:** Organic shapes and rounded corners evoke softness and approachability. Breathing room between elements mirrors the intentional calm the app encourages. No sharp edges or sterile clinical aesthetics.\n14\t\n15\t---\n16\t\n17\t## 2. Color Palette\n18\t\n19\t### Light Theme\n20\t\n21\t- **Lavender Bloom** (#7C3AED) — Primary brand color, used for key actions, navigation highlights, and the primary AppBar. Provides confident yet gentle presence.\n22\t- **Blush Rose** (#F9A8D4) — Secondary accent, used for mood emojis, mood trend highlights, and decorative touches that feel warm and nurturing.\n23\t- **Soft Mint** (#6EE7B7) — Tertiary color for success states, checkmarks, and positive confirmations. Subtle and reassuring.\n24\t- **Morning Mist** (#FAFAFA) — Card and surface backgrounds. Clean without being stark white.\n25\t- **Lavender Tint** (#F5F3FF) — Scaffold background. A gentle purple-tinted wash that unifies the visual experience.\n26\t- **Deep Graphite** (#1F2937) — Primary text color. Softer than pure black, easier on the eyes during extended reading.\n27\t- **Stone Grey** (#6B7280) — Secondary text, captions, timestamps, and supporting labels.\n28\t- **Misty Border** (#E5E7EB) — Borders, dividers, and subtle structural lines. Barely-there structure.\n29\t- **Soft Coral** (#EF4444) — Error states, validation messages, destructive actions. Stands out without alarm.\n30\t- **Warm White** (#FFFFFF) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces.\n31\t\n32\t### Dark Theme\n33\t\n34\t- **Twilight Bloom** (#9F67FF) — Primary brand in dark mode. Slightly lighter and warmer than the light primary to maintain softness in low-light conditions.\n35\t- **Dusky Rose** (#FBC4E0) — Secondary accent for dark mode. Warmer and more luminous than the light secondary.\n36\t- **Night Mint** (#34D399) — Tertiary success color for dark mode. More vibrant to stand out against dark surfaces.\n37\t- **Deep Twilight** (#1E1B2E) — Card and surface backgrounds in dark mode. Warm-tinted dark purple-grey, never cold.\n38\t- **Night Sky** (#13111C) — Scaffold background in dark mode. Deep but warm, avoiding pure black.\n39\t- **Soft Pearl** (#F3F4F6) — Primary text in dark mode. High contrast but not harsh.\n40\t- **Muted Silver** (#9CA3AF) — Secondary text, captions, and supporting labels in dark mode.\n41\t- **Deep Border** (#2D2B3A) — Borders, dividers, and structural lines in dark mode. Subtle but visible.\n42\t- **Muted Coral** (#F87171) — Error states in dark mode. Slightly softer red to maintain the warm tone.\n43\t- **Charcoal Surface** (#252336) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces in dark mode.\n44\t\n45\t### Neutral Scale (Light Theme)\n46\t- **Ivory** (#FAFAF9)\n47\t- **Pearl** (#F5F5F4)\n48\t- **Stone 100** (#F5F5F4)\n49\t- **Stone 200** (#E7E5E4)\n50\t- **Stone 300** (#D6D3D1)\n51\t- **Stone 400** (#A8A29E)\n52\t- **Stone 500** (#78716C)\n53\t- **Stone 600** (#57534E)\n54\t- **Stone 700** (#44403C)\n55\t- **Stone 800** (#292524)\n56\t- **Stone 900** (#1C1917)\n57\t\n58\t### Neutral Scale (Dark Theme)\n59\t- **Night Ivory** (#1A1825)\n60\t- **Night Pearl** (#252336)\n61\t- **Night Stone 100** (#2D2B3A)\n62\t- **Night Stone 200** (#3D3A4D)\n63\t- **Night Stone 300** (#4D4A5E)\n64\t- **Night Stone 400** (#6B6880)\n65\t- **Night Stone 500** (#8B8899)\n66\t- **Night Stone 600** (#ABABB9)\n67\t- **Night Stone 700** (#CBCAD0)\n68\t- **Night Stone 800** (#E5E4E8)\n69\t- **Night Stone 900** (#F3F4F6)\n70\t\n71\t---\n72\t\n73\t## 3. Typography\n74\t\n75\t### Font Selection\n76\t\n77\t- **Display Font:** Nunito — Rounded, friendly letterforms with a warm, approachable character. Excellent for headlines and large text where softness and readability are paramount. Nunito's terminals and joints have a gentle, open quality that avoids feeling sharp or clinical. Used for: Hero display, screen titles, section headers.\n78\t\n79\t- **Body Font:** Nunito — The same family is used for body text to maintain visual cohesion. At reading sizes, Nunito's proportions provide comfortable extended reading without fatigue. Used for: Body text, labels, captions, button text, chips.\n80\t\n81\t### Type Scale\n82\t\n83\t| Role | Font | Weight | Size | Line Height | Usage |\n84\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n85\t| Hero display | Nunito | Bold (700) | 57pt | 64pt | Splash screens, week number display on pregnancy hero |\n86\t| Screen title | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 28pt | 36pt | Top-level screen headings |\n87\t| Section header | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 22pt | 28pt | Card titles, section headers within screens |\n88\t| Subtitle | Nunito | Medium (500) | 16pt | 24pt | List item titles, subtitles, chart labels |\n89\t| Body | Nunito | Regular (400) | 16pt | 24pt | Primary reading text, article body |\n90\t| Body small | Nunito | Regular (400) | 14pt | 20pt | Secondary text, descriptions, log entry details |\n91\t| Button label | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 14pt | 20pt | Button text, chip labels, navigation items |\n92\t| Caption | Nunito | Medium (500) | 11pt | 16pt | Badges, timestamps, tab labels, small metadata |\n93\t\n94\t### Letter Spacing Guidelines\n95\t\n96\t- Hero display: 0pt (set solid)\n97\t- Screen titles: -0.5pt (slight tightening for large type)\n98\t- Body text: 0.15pt (open, readable spacing)\n99\t- Caption and labels: 0.4pt (clear separation for small text)\n100\t\n101\t---\n102\t\n103\t## 4. Component Styles\n104\t\n105\t### Card\n106\t- **Corner radius:** 16 points\n107\t- **Shadow depth:** Soft, diffused shadow — 8 points blur, 2 points offset-y, rgba(0,0,0,0.08) in light mode; rgba(0,0,0,0.25) in dark mode. The shadow feels like gentle morning light creating a soft pool beneath the card.\n108\t- **Background:** Morning Mist (#FAFAFA) in light mode; Deep Twilight (#1E1B2E) in dark mode\n109\t- **Internal padding:** 16 points all sides; 20 points for cards containing action buttons\n110\t- **Tap feedback:** Subtle scale-down to 98% on press, with 200ms ease-out return. The press feels like a gentle press into a soft surface rather than a click.\n111\t- **Spacing between cards:** 12 points\n112\t\n113\t### Buttons\n114\t\n115\t**Primary Button**\n116\t- Shape: Pill-shaped (fully rounded on all corners, corner radius equals half the button height)\n117\t- Minimum height: 48 points (touch target compliance)\n118\t- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n119\t- Text: White (#FFFFFF), SemiBold, 14pt\n120\t- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background darkens by 8% brightness\n121\t- Corner radius: 24 points (fully rounded pill)\n122\t\n123\t**Secondary Button**\n124\t- Shape: Pill-shaped\n125\t- Minimum height: 48 points\n126\t- Background: Transparent with Lavender Bloom border (2 points stroke) in light mode; Transparent with Twilight Bloom border in dark mode\n127\t- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n128\t- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background fills with 10% primary color\n129\t- Corner radius: 24 points\n130\t\n131\t**Text Button**\n132\t- Shape: No background, no border\n133\t- Minimum height: 48 points\n134\t- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Text button inherits no background, only color\n135\t- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out opacity reduction to 60%\n136\t\n137\t**FAB (Floating Action Button)**\n138\t- Size: 56 points diameter\n139\t- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED); Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n140\t- Icon: White, 24 points\n141\t- Shadow: Medium diffused shadow, 12 points blur\n142\t- Press feedback: 200ms scale to 90%, shadow intensifies slightly\n143\t\n144\t### Text Input\n145\t- **Decoration style:** Filled background — a rounded container that feels like a gentle trough for text\n146\t- **Corner radius:** 12 points\n147\t- **Fill color:** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n148\t- **Border:** None at rest; on focus, a 2-point Lavender Bloom border appears with smooth 200ms transition\n149\t- **Label behavior:** Floating label that rises above the field on focus or when content is present; label color transitions from Stone 400 (#A8A29E) to Lavender Bloom on focus\n150\t- **Error state:** Border becomes Soft Coral (#EF4444), error message appears below in Soft Coral, 14pt\n151\t- **Minimum height:** 56 points to ensure comfortable touch interaction\n152\t\n153\t### Chip\n154\t- **Shape:** Fully rounded pill (corner radius = half the chip height)\n155\t- **Corner radius:** 16 points (pill shape)\n156\t- **Background (default):** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n157\t- **Background (selected):** Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity (#7C3AED1A), with Lavender Bloom text\n158\t- **Minimum height:** 32 points (comfortable touch target)\n159\t- **Horizontal padding:** 12 points left and right\n160\t- **Tap feedback:** 150ms opacity shift to selected state, no scale change (chips feel like gentle toggles, not buttons)\n161\t\n162\t### Bottom Sheet\n163\t- **Top corner radius:** 28 points — large, prominent rounding that feels organic and soft\n164\t- **Background:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n165\t- **Handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered at top, Stone 300 (#D6D3D1) color in light mode; Night Stone 200 in dark mode. The handle feels like a gentle grip point, not structural.\n166\t- **Maximum height:** 90% of screen height for full sheets; 50% for half sheets\n167\t- **Shadow:** Soft diffused shadow, 16 points blur, 4 points offset-y\n168\t- **Open animation:** 250ms smooth deceleration — slides up from bottom edge with subtle fade\n169\t\n170\t### Navigation Bar (Bottom Tabs)\n171\t- **Background color:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n172\t- **Active indicator:** A small rounded pill beneath the active tab icon and label. The pill is filled with Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity. The indicator transitions smoothly (200ms) between tabs.\n173\t- **Icon style:** Outlined icons for inactive state, filled icons for active state — the active tab is visually \"filled\" with color\n174\t- **Icon size:** 24 points\n175\t- **Label visibility:** Labels are always visible below icons — no hidden label behavior. Text is SemiBold 11pt when active, Regular 11pt when inactive.\n176\t- **Touch target:** Each tab item has a minimum 48-point touch target height\n177\t- **Safe area:** Bottom navigation respects the home indicator area on notched devices\n178\t\n179\t### App Bar\n180\t- **Background:** Transparent to scaffold background color (Lavender Tint #F5F3FF in light mode; Night Sky #13111C in dark mode). The AppBar feels like it floats over the content.\n181\t- **Title text style:** SemiBold 20pt, Deep Graphite (#1F2937) in light mode; Soft Pearl (#F3F4F6) in dark mode\n182\t- **Scroll behavior:** On scrollable content, the AppBar has a subtle fade-in effect as content scrolls beneath it. On screens with SliverAppBar, the AppBar collapses to show a smaller representation.\n183\t- **Leading/back button:** Icon button with 48-point touch target, Lavender Bloom on tap\n184\t\n185\t---\n186\t\n187\t## 5. Layout Principles\n188\t\n189\t- **Base spacing unit:** 8 points — all spacing is derived from multiples of 8\n190\t- **Screen horizontal padding:** 16 points from each edge\n191\t- **Section vertical spacing:** 24 points between major sections\n192\t- **Card internal padding:** 16 points all sides\n193\t- **Card gap:** 12 points between cards in a grid or list\n194\t- **List item minimum height:** 56 points (comfortable touch target for interactive list items)\n195\t- **Minimum touch target:** 48 points (compliant with mobile accessibility standards)\n196\t- **Bottom sheet handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered 20 points from top\n197\t- **Safe area awareness:** Respect status bar at top (add 12 points padding when status bar is visible) and home indicator at bottom (bottom navigation and FAB account for this)\n198\t- **Grid gutters:** 12 points between columns in 2-column grids\n199\t- **Card corner radius:** 16 points for standard cards; 12 points for smaller card variants\n200\t\n201\t---\n202\t\n203\t## 6. Motion & Animation\n204\t\n205\tMotion is gentle, purposeful, and never jarring. The app feels like a calm, flowing experience rather than a reactive, mechanical one.\n206\t\n207\t- **Page transitions:** 300ms duration, smooth deceleration. Screen content slides and fades simultaneously — the new screen appears to gently settle into place.\n208\t- **Micro-interactions:** 200ms duration, snappy ease-out. Button presses, chip selections, toggle switches — responses feel quick but soft, like a gentle tap on a responsive surface.\n209\t- **Hero transitions:** 350ms duration, fast-out-slow-in easing. When navigating from a list to a detail view (e.g., article reader), shared elements like images and titles smoothly expand and continue their motion arc.\n210\t- **Staggered list reveals:** 50ms delay between each item. When content loads, list items cascade into view in a waterfall — items appear 50ms apart, creating a sense of gentle unfolding rather than a sudden dump of content.\n211\t- **Bottom sheets:** 250ms duration, smooth deceleration. Sheets slide up from the bottom edge, decelerating naturally as they reach their resting position.\n212\t- **Pull-to-refresh:** 150ms duration, quick snap. The refresh indicator appears and dismisses quickly but not abruptly.\n213\t- **Tab indicator movement:** 200ms duration, ease-in-out. The active indicator pill smoothly glides between tab positions.\n214\t- **Card tap feedback:** 200ms ease-out scale to 98%, then 200ms ease-out return to 100%.\n215\t- **FAB appearance:** 200ms fade-in with subtle scale from 95% to 100%.\n216\t\n217\t---\n218\t\n219\t## 7. Anti-Patterns (Banned Design Rules)\n220\t\n221\t- No default platform colors — every color comes from the design system palette\n222\t- No ad-hoc text sizing — all text uses the defined type scale\n223\t- No inconsistent spacing — all spacing uses the 8-point base unit scale\n224\t- No arbitrary elevation — every shadow level communicates a specific hierarchy\n225\t- No Inter or Roboto — Nunito is the only font family\n226\t- No purple or neon AI aesthetic — colors are warm pastels, not synthetic\n227\t- No generic gradients — backgrounds are flat or subtly tinted, not gradient-washed\n228\t- No shadows without purpose — elevation always communicates hierarchy\n229\t- No desktop patterns — no sidebars, hover tooltips, right-click menus, or desktop-only interaction patterns\n230\t- No touch targets smaller than 48 points\n231\t- No critical actions outside the thumb zone (bottom two-thirds of screen height)\n232\t- No pure black (#000000) anywhere — deep charcoal and off-black only\n233\t- No pure white (#FFFFFF) for text — use off-white tones that reduce eye strain"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f062649-0c01-450d-a85b-f7569af9b4e9","uuid":"b961f1c0-afef-4455-a7c0-49fb240bf404","timestamp":"2026-05-19T02:18:49.392Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/minh/Documents/openplayboosks/examples/baby-app/.stitch/system/DESIGN.md","content":"# Pregnant Tracker - Baby Bump — Design System\n\n## 1. Visual Theme\n\n**Theme Name:** Gentle Bloom\n\n**Mood:** A soft, nurturing sanctuary — warm natural light filtering through a nursery window, reassuring and calm without being clinical or sterile.\n\n**Light Mode (Primary):** Light mode is the primary experience. The interface feels like morning sunlight in a cozy, plant-filled nursery — airy, warm, and welcoming.\n\n**Dark Mode (Secondary):** Deep twilight tones that maintain the warmth of the light palette. Not cold charcoal — more like a softly lit nursery at dusk with warm accent lighting.\n\n**Key Visual Metaphors:** Organic shapes and rounded corners evoke softness and approachability. Breathing room between elements mirrors the intentional calm the app encourages. No sharp edges or sterile clinical aesthetics.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Color Palette\n\n### Light Theme\n\n- **Lavender Bloom** (#7C3AED) — Primary brand color, used for key actions, navigation highlights, and the primary AppBar. Provides confident yet gentle presence.\n- **Blush Rose** (#F9A8D4) — Secondary accent, used for mood emojis, mood trend highlights, and decorative touches that feel warm and nurturing.\n- **Soft Mint** (#6EE7B7) — Tertiary color for success states, checkmarks, and positive confirmations. Subtle and reassuring.\n- **Morning Mist** (#FAFAFA) — Card and surface backgrounds. Clean without being stark white.\n- **Lavender Tint** (#F5F3FF) — Scaffold background. A gentle purple-tinted wash that unifies the visual experience.\n- **Deep Graphite** (#1F2937) — Primary text color. Softer than pure black, easier on the eyes during extended reading.\n- **Stone Grey** (#6B7280) — Secondary text, captions, timestamps, and supporting labels.\n- **Misty Border** (#E5E7EB) — Borders, dividers, and subtle structural lines. Barely-there structure.\n- **Soft Coral** (#EF4444) — Error states, validation messages, destructive actions. Stands out without alarm.\n- **Warm White** (#FFFFFF) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces.\n\n### Dark Theme\n\n- **Twilight Bloom** (#9F67FF) — Primary brand in dark mode. Slightly lighter and warmer than the light primary to maintain softness in low-light conditions.\n- **Dusky Rose** (#FBC4E0) — Secondary accent for dark mode. Warmer and more luminous than the light secondary.\n- **Night Mint** (#34D399) — Tertiary success color for dark mode. More vibrant to stand out against dark surfaces.\n- **Deep Twilight** (#1E1B2E) — Card and surface backgrounds in dark mode. Warm-tinted dark purple-grey, never cold.\n- **Night Sky** (#13111C) — Scaffold background in dark mode. Deep but warm, avoiding pure black.\n- **Soft Pearl** (#F3F4F6) — Primary text in dark mode. High contrast but not harsh.\n- **Muted Silver** (#9CA3AF) — Secondary text, captions, and supporting labels in dark mode.\n- **Deep Border** (#2D2B3A) — Borders, dividers, and structural lines in dark mode. Subtle but visible.\n- **Muted Coral** (#F87171) — Error states in dark mode. Slightly softer red to maintain the warm tone.\n- **Charcoal Surface** (#252336) — Bottom navigation bar background, sheets, and dialog surfaces in dark mode.\n\n### Neutral Scale (Light Theme)\n- **Ivory** (#FAFAF9)\n- **Pearl** (#F5F5F4)\n- **Stone 100** (#F5F5F4)\n- **Stone 200** (#E7E5E4)\n- **Stone 300** (#D6D3D1)\n- **Stone 400** (#A8A29E)\n- **Stone 500** (#78716C)\n- **Stone 600** (#57534E)\n- **Stone 700** (#44403C)\n- **Stone 800** (#292524)\n- **Stone 900** (#1C1917)\n\n### Neutral Scale (Dark Theme)\n- **Night Ivory** (#1A1825)\n- **Night Pearl** (#252336)\n- **Night Stone 100** (#2D2B3A)\n- **Night Stone 200** (#3D3A4D)\n- **Night Stone 300** (#4D4A5E)\n- **Night Stone 400** (#6B6880)\n- **Night Stone 500** (#8B8899)\n- **Night Stone 600** (#ABABB9)\n- **Night Stone 700** (#CBCAD0)\n- **Night Stone 800** (#E5E4E8)\n- **Night Stone 900** (#F3F4F6)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Typography\n\n### Font Selection\n\n- **Display Font:** Nunito — Rounded, friendly letterforms with a warm, approachable character. Excellent for headlines and large text where softness and readability are paramount. Nunito's terminals and joints have a gentle, open quality that avoids feeling sharp or clinical. Used for: Hero display, screen titles, section headers.\n\n- **Body Font:** Nunito — The same family is used for body text to maintain visual cohesion. At reading sizes, Nunito's proportions provide comfortable extended reading without fatigue. Used for: Body text, labels, captions, button text, chips.\n\n### Type Scale\n\n| Role | Font | Weight | Size | Line Height | Usage |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Hero display | Nunito | Bold (700) | 57pt | 64pt | Splash screens, week number display on pregnancy hero |\n| Screen title | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 28pt | 36pt | Top-level screen headings |\n| Section header | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 22pt | 28pt | Card titles, section headers within screens |\n| Subtitle | Nunito | Medium (500) | 16pt | 24pt | List item titles, subtitles, chart labels |\n| Body | Nunito | Regular (400) | 16pt | 24pt | Primary reading text, article body |\n| Body small | Nunito | Regular (400) | 14pt | 20pt | Secondary text, descriptions, log entry details |\n| Button label | Nunito | SemiBold (600) | 14pt | 20pt | Button text, chip labels, navigation items |\n| Caption | Nunito | Medium (500) | 11pt | 16pt | Badges, timestamps, tab labels, small metadata |\n\n### Letter Spacing Guidelines\n\n- Hero display: 0pt (set solid)\n- Screen titles: -0.5pt (slight tightening for large type)\n- Body text: 0.15pt (open, readable spacing)\n- Caption and labels: 0.4pt (clear separation for small text)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Component Styles\n\n### Card\n- **Corner radius:** 16 points\n- **Shadow depth:** Soft, diffused shadow — 8 points blur, 2 points offset-y, rgba(0,0,0,0.08) in light mode; rgba(0,0,0,0.25) in dark mode. The shadow feels like gentle morning light creating a soft pool beneath the card.\n- **Background:** Morning Mist (#FAFAFA) in light mode; Deep Twilight (#1E1B2E) in dark mode\n- **Internal padding:** 16 points all sides; 20 points for cards containing action buttons\n- **Tap feedback:** Subtle scale-down to 98% on press, with 200ms ease-out return. The press feels like a gentle press into a soft surface rather than a click.\n- **Spacing between cards:** 12 points\n\n### Buttons\n\n**Primary Button**\n- Shape: Pill-shaped (fully rounded on all corners, corner radius equals half the button height)\n- Minimum height: 48 points (touch target compliance)\n- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n- Text: White (#FFFFFF), SemiBold, 14pt\n- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background darkens by 8% brightness\n- Corner radius: 24 points (fully rounded pill)\n\n**Secondary Button**\n- Shape: Pill-shaped\n- Minimum height: 48 points\n- Background: Transparent with Lavender Bloom border (2 points stroke) in light mode; Transparent with Twilight Bloom border in dark mode\n- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out scale to 95%, background fills with 10% primary color\n- Corner radius: 24 points\n\n**Text Button**\n- Shape: No background, no border\n- Minimum height: 48 points\n- Text: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED) in light mode; Text button inherits no background, only color\n- Press feedback: 200ms ease-out opacity reduction to 60%\n\n**FAB (Floating Action Button)**\n- Size: 56 points diameter\n- Background: Lavender Bloom (#7C3AED); Twilight Bloom (#9F67FF) in dark mode\n- Icon: White, 24 points\n- Shadow: Medium diffused shadow, 12 points blur\n- Press feedback: 200ms scale to 90%, shadow intensifies slightly\n\n### Text Input\n- **Decoration style:** Filled background — a rounded container that feels like a gentle trough for text\n- **Corner radius:** 12 points\n- **Fill color:** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n- **Border:** None at rest; on focus, a 2-point Lavender Bloom border appears with smooth 200ms transition\n- **Label behavior:** Floating label that rises above the field on focus or when content is present; label color transitions from Stone 400 (#A8A29E) to Lavender Bloom on focus\n- **Error state:** Border becomes Soft Coral (#EF4444), error message appears below in Soft Coral, 14pt\n- **Minimum height:** 56 points to ensure comfortable touch interaction\n\n### Chip\n- **Shape:** Fully rounded pill (corner radius = half the chip height)\n- **Corner radius:** 16 points (pill shape)\n- **Background (default):** Stone 100 (#F5F5F4) in light mode; Night Stone 100 (#2D2B3A) in dark mode\n- **Background (selected):** Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity (#7C3AED1A), with Lavender Bloom text\n- **Minimum height:** 32 points (comfortable touch target)\n- **Horizontal padding:** 12 points left and right\n- **Tap feedback:** 150ms opacity shift to selected state, no scale change (chips feel like gentle toggles, not buttons)\n\n### Bottom Sheet\n- **Top corner radius:** 28 points — large, prominent rounding that feels organic and soft\n- **Background:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n- **Handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered at top, Stone 300 (#D6D3D1) color in light mode; Night Stone 200 in dark mode. The handle feels like a gentle grip point, not structural.\n- **Maximum height:** 90% of screen height for full sheets; 50% for half sheets\n- **Shadow:** Soft diffused shadow, 16 points blur, 4 points offset-y\n- **Open animation:** 250ms smooth deceleration — slides up from bottom edge with subtle fade\n\n### Navigation Bar (Bottom Tabs)\n- **Background color:** Warm White (#FFFFFF) in light mode; Charcoal Surface (#252336) in dark mode\n- **Active indicator:** A small rounded pill beneath the active tab icon and label. The pill is filled with Lavender Bloom at 15% opacity. The indicator transitions smoothly (200ms) between tabs.\n- **Icon style:** Outlined icons for inactive state, filled icons for active state — the active tab is visually \"filled\" with color\n- **Icon size:** 24 points\n- **Label visibility:** Labels are always visible below icons — no hidden label behavior. Text is SemiBold 11pt when active, Regular 11pt when inactive.\n- **Touch target:** Each tab item has a minimum 48-point touch target height\n- **Safe area:** Bottom navigation respects the home indicator area on notched devices\n\n### App Bar\n- **Background:** Transparent to scaffold background color (Lavender Tint #F5F3FF in light mode; Night Sky #13111C in dark mode). The AppBar feels like it floats over the content.\n- **Title text style:** SemiBold 20pt, Deep Graphite (#1F2937) in light mode; Soft Pearl (#F3F4F6) in dark mode\n- **Scroll behavior:** On scrollable content, the AppBar has a subtle fade-in effect as content scrolls beneath it. On screens with SliverAppBar, the AppBar collapses to show a smaller representation.\n- **Leading/back button:** Icon button with 48-point touch target, Lavender Bloom on tap\n\n---\n\n## 5. Layout Principles\n\n- **Base spacing unit:** 8 points — all spacing is derived from multiples of 8\n- **Screen horizontal padding:** 16 points from each edge\n- **Section vertical spacing:** 24 points between major sections\n- **Card internal padding:** 16 points all sides\n- **Card gap:** 12 points between cards in a grid or list\n- **List item minimum height:** 56 points (comfortable touch target for interactive list items)\n- **Minimum touch target:** 48 points (compliant with mobile accessibility standards)\n- **Bottom sheet handle bar:** 40 points wide, 4 points tall, centered 20 points from top\n- **Safe area awareness:** Respect status bar at top (add 12 points padding when status bar is visible) and home indicator at bottom (bottom navigation and FAB account for this)\n- **Grid gutters:** 12 points between columns in 2-column grids\n- **Card corner radius:** 16 points for standard cards; 12 points for smaller card variants\n\n---\n\n## 6. Motion & Animation\n\nMotion is gentle, purposeful, and never jarring. The app feels like a calm, flowing experience rather than a reactive, mechanical one.\n\n- **Page transitions:** 300ms duration, smooth deceleration. Screen content slides and fades simultaneously — the new screen appears to gently settle into place.\n- **Micro-interactions:** 200ms duration, snappy ease-out. Button presses, chip selections, toggle switches — responses feel quick but soft, like a gentle tap on a responsive surface.\n- **Hero transitions:** 350ms duration, fast-out-slow-in easing. When navigating from a list to a detail view (e.g., article reader), shared elements like images and titles smoothly expand and continue their motion arc.\n- **Staggered list reveals:** 50ms delay between each item. When content loads, list items cascade into view in a waterfall — items appear 50ms apart, creating a sense of gentle unfolding rather than a sudden dump of content.\n- **Bottom sheets:** 250ms duration, smooth deceleration. Sheets slide up from the bottom edge, decelerating naturally as they reach their resting position.\n- **Pull-to-refresh:** 150ms duration, quick snap. The refresh indicator appears and dismisses quickly but not abruptly.\n- **Tab indicator movement:** 200ms duration, ease-in-out. The active indicator pill smoothly glides between tab positions.\n- **Card tap feedback:** 200ms ease-out scale to 98%, then 200ms ease-out return to 100%.\n- **FAB appearance:** 200ms fade-in with subtle scale from 95% to 100%.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Anti-Patterns (Banned Design Rules)\n\n- No default platform colors — every color comes from the design system palette\n- No ad-hoc text sizing — all text uses the defined type scale\n- No inconsistent spacing — all spacing uses the 8-point base unit scale\n- No arbitrary elevation — every shadow level communicates a specific hierarchy\n- No Inter or Roboto — Nunito is the only font family\n- No purple or neon AI aesthetic — colors are warm pastels, not synthetic\n- No generic gradients — backgrounds are flat or subtly tinted, not gradient-washed\n- No shadows without purpose — elevation always communicates hierarchy\n- No desktop patterns — no sidebars, hover tooltips, right-click menus, or desktop-only interaction patterns\n- No touch targets smaller than 48 points\n- No critical actions outside the thumb zone (bottom two-thirds of screen height)\n- No pure black (#000000) anywhere — deep charcoal and off-black only\n- No pure white (#FFFFFF) for text — use off-white tones that reduce eye strain","numLines":233,"startLine":1,"totalLines":233}}}
